### CRIT-02: Generic `query<T>()` helper defaults to `SELECT *` with no pagination
**File:** `src/lib/data/server.ts:22-57`
**Severity:** CRITICAL
```typescript
// server.ts:34
let q = supabase.from(table).select(opts?.select ?? "*");
// No default limit applied -- unbounded result set
```
**Impact:**
- 30+ server-side functions use `query<T>()` without specifying a `select` or `limit`
- Every call fetches ALL columns and ALL matching rows
- Functions affected (all unbounded):
  - `getAppointments()` (line 293) -- all appointments for a clinic
  - `getAppointmentsByDoctor()` (line 300) -- all appointments for a doctor
  - `getAppointmentsByPatient()` (line 307) -- all appointments for a patient
  - `getNotifications()` (line 438) -- all notifications for a user
  - `getConsultationNotes()` (line 538) -- all notes for a clinic
  - `getWaitingList()` (line 562) -- all waiting list entries
  - `getProducts()` (line 742) -- all products
  - `getStock()` (line 763) -- all stock entries
  - `getLabOrders()` (line 658) -- all lab orders
  - `getSterilizationLog()` (line 712) -- all sterilization entries
  - `getPrescriptionRequests()` (line 812) -- all prescription requests
  - `getLoyaltyPoints()` (line 842) -- all loyalty records
  - `getTreatmentPlans()` (line 625) -- all treatment plans (no clinic_id filter when doctorId is empty!)
  - And 15+ more
**Remediation:**
- Add a default limit to `query<T>()` (e.g., `q = q.limit(opts?.limit ?? 1000)`) as `fetchRows<T>()` already does on the client side
- Require callers to explicitly pass `select` columns
- Add cursor-based pagination for list endpoints
