## HIGH Findings
### HIGH-01: `ensureLookups()` fetches ALL users and services per clinic on every page
**File:** `src/lib/data/client.ts:164-184`
**Severity:** HIGH
```typescript
async function ensureLookups(clinicId: string) {
  if (_userMap && _serviceMap && Date.now() - _lookupsBuiltAt < CACHE_TTL_MS) return;
  const [usersRes, servicesRes] = await Promise.all([
    supabase.from("users").select("id, name, phone, email").eq("clinic_id", clinicId),
    supabase.from("services").select("id, name, price").eq("clinic_id", clinicId),
  ]);
  // ...builds Maps from ALL results
}
```
**Impact:**
- Fetches ALL users (patients + doctors + staff) for a clinic -- could be thousands
- Called by 20+ client-side fetch functions (appointments, reviews, prescriptions, treatment plans, etc.)
- 5-minute cache TTL means this fires every 5 minutes per active session
- No Supabase default limit applied -- silent truncation at 1,000 rows
  - If clinic has >1,000 users, the lookup map is INCOMPLETE and patient names show as "Patient"
**Remediation:**
- Limit the user lookup to roles that are actually needed for display (doctors, staff) -- patients can be fetched per-query via joins
- Or use Supabase foreign-key joins (`select("*, patient:patient_id(name)")`) to fetch names inline
- Add explicit `.limit()` or paginate
