### HIGH-02: Backup module uses SELECT * on 9 tables sequentially
**File:** `src/lib/backup.ts:85-91`
**Severity:** HIGH
```typescript
for (const table of BACKUP_TABLES) {
  const { data: rows, error } = await supabase
    .from(table)
    .select("*")
    .eq("clinic_id", clinicId)
    .order("created_at", { ascending: false })
    .limit(MAX_ROWS_PER_TABLE); // 10,000
}
```
**Impact:**
- Sequential SELECT * on 9 tables, up to 10,000 rows each = up to 90,000 rows loaded into memory
- All data held in a single JS object before JSON serialization
- Potential OOM on large clinics
- Tables include `notifications` (high volume) and `appointments` (high volume)
**Remediation:**
- Stream data in chunks using Supabase range queries
- Select only columns needed for backup (exclude computed/derived columns)
- Consider server-side pg_dump for large backups
