### MED-05: Redundant `ensureLookups()` calls in page-level compositions
**File:** `src/lib/data/client.ts` (multiple locations)
**Severity:** MEDIUM
When a page calls multiple fetch functions, each one calls `ensureLookups()`:
```
fetchAppointments()      -> ensureLookups()  (cached after first call)
fetchConsultationNotes() -> ensureLookups()  (cache hit)
fetchPrescriptions()     -> ensureLookups()  (cache hit)
fetchWaitingList()       -> ensureLookups()  (cache hit)
```
**Impact:**
- First call in a session downloads ALL users + ALL services
- Subsequent calls hit cache (5-min TTL) -- but on page load, 4+ functions may call ensureLookups simultaneously before the first one resolves
- Race condition: multiple concurrent ensureLookups() calls may fire 2+ parallel fetches of ALL users
- No mutex/lock on the cache check
