## Data Volume Risk Assessment
### Tier 1: Critical Growth Tables
| Table | Growth Pattern | Risk | Mitigation Status |
|-------|---------------|------|-------------------|
| `appointments` | +N per doctor per day | HIGH -- unbounded queries in 5+ functions, analytics fetches ALL rows | NO mitigation |
| `notifications` | +N per appointment (reminders, confirmations) | HIGH -- grows faster than appointments, no pagination on read | NO mitigation |
| `payments` | +1 per appointment | MEDIUM -- dashboard sums ALL payments | NO mitigation |
| `notification_log` | +1 per sent reminder | MEDIUM -- queried by cron with `.in()` | Partial (limit 500 in cron) |
### Tier 2: Moderate Growth Tables
| Table | Growth Pattern | Risk | Mitigation Status |
|-------|---------------|------|-------------------|
| `consultation_notes` | +1 per appointment | LOW-MEDIUM -- no pagination | NO mitigation |
| `prescriptions` | +1 per consultation | LOW-MEDIUM -- no pagination | NO mitigation |
| `reviews` | +1 per patient visit | LOW -- moderate growth | NO mitigation |
| `documents` | +N per patient | LOW-MEDIUM -- file metadata grows with uploads | NO mitigation |
| `lab_test_orders` | +1 per test order | LOW-MEDIUM -- 4-query pattern for list | NO mitigation |
| `lab_test_results` | +N per order | LOW -- only queried per-order | OK |
### Tier 3: Low Growth Tables
| Table | Notes |
|-------|-------|
| `users` | Grows slowly, but fetched entirely by `ensureLookups()` |
| `services` | Low cardinality, fetched entirely by `ensureLookups()` |
| `clinics` | Very low cardinality |
| `time_slots` | Low cardinality (7 days * N doctors) |
| `products` | Moderate -- pharmacy inventory |
| `stock` | 1:1 with products |
